cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.MA, cs.ES

The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks (ANNs) and proposes a spin-transfer-torque (STT) device based on domain wall motion (DWM) magnetic strip to implement a soft-limiting non-linear neuron (SNN) for low power ANNs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of post-CMOS devices, which suggests a possible fit with cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), and the use of micro-magnetic simulation, which suggests a possible fit with cs.EM (Electromagnetism). The paper also presents an ANN hardware design, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.ES (Embedded Systems).
